In this article, President Donald Trump issues a proclamation recognizing Emergency Medical Services (EMS) Week and pays tribute to EMS providers who save lives every day. He acknowledges the critical role of EMS personnel as the first link to emergency medical care and highlights their selfless dedication and extraordinary efforts. The article also mentions the challenges faced by EMS agencies, particularly in rural areas, and the steps taken by the administration to support them, such as reauthorizing funding and implementing the Emergency Triage, Treat, and Transport model. President Trump also emphasizes the role of EMS providers in addressing the opioid crisis and ensuring they have the necessary training and resources. The proclamation concludes by urging all Americans to show their support for local EMS professionals during EMS Week.